      <learningContent id="learncont-d7f467ee-c958-4cc8-a784-6ae3ac8bc1fd">
        <title>Removing the Stem</title>
        <lcInstruction id="lci-d99a2686-ae9e-44b8-b5a5-5a36975f96d1">
          <description>
            <para>
To remove the stem, first remove the handlebar (refer to <dmRef xlink:type="simple" xlink:actuate="onRequest" xlink:show="new" xlink:href="URN:S1000D:DMC-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA2-20-00-00AA-520A-T-T45-C_001-00"><dmRefIdent><dmCode modelIdentCode="S1000DBIKE" systemDiffCode="AAA" systemCode="DA2" subSystemCode="2" subSubSystemCode="0" assyCode="00" disassyCode="00" disassyCodeVariant="AA" infoCode="520" infoCodeVariant="A" itemLocationCode="T" learnCode="T45" learnEventCode="C" /></dmRefIdent><dmRefAddressItems><dmTitle><techName>Handlebar</techName><infoName>Remove procedures</infoName></dmTitle></dmRefAddressItems><behavior linkShow="newPane" linkActuate="onRequest" /></dmRef>).
			</para>
            <para>Next, remove the bolt in the center of the stem cap. Use an Allen wrench to loosen the stem cap bolt.</para>
            <para>Remove the clamp bolts.</para>
            <para>Remove the stem from the steerer tube.</para>
            <note>
              <notePara>Do not tighten the stem bolt too much. You can cause damage to the headset bearings if you tighten the stem too much.</notePara>
            </note>
